			},
					3372: {
				id_comment: 3372,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "‘In summoning’; the Latin appears to mean ‘when he had summoned’, but this is probably not the sense of the Greek, and indeed it is hard to see how the bestowal of glory on Christians could be represented as earlier in time than the Crucifixion. It seems likely, therefore, that the sense intended by the Latin is, ‘since he had decided to summon a multitude of his sons to glory’."
			},
