				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "Is. 8.17 and 18. ‘And then’ is expressed by the same word as ‘and elsewhere’; but here the Apostle seems to be drawing our attention to the connexion of thought between two consecutive verses of Isaias. That confidence with which the prophet inspires his own disciples is regarded as the type of that faith which our Lord communicates to Christian people."
			},
					3375: {
				id_comment: 3375,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "‘After all, he does not make himself the angels’ champion’; literally, according to the Latin, ‘he does not anywhere take the angels’, which some have interpreted as meaning, ‘he does not take upon himself the nature of angels’; but this interpretation does not accord well with the Greek."
			},
